patthana11.2:0.2_0: (This should be expanded as in MN 4.)
patthana11.2:0.3_0: These are the different kinds of result.
patthana11.2:1.1_0: There is no skilled in the dark result of the unskillful result of deeds.
patthana11.2:1.1_1: There is no skilled in the ways of doing unskillful deeds.
patthana11.2:1.1_2: There is no such thing as the unskillful result of past deeds, but not the result of deeds.
patthana11.2:1.1_3: There are no unskillful qualities that arise because of the unskillful or not.
patthana11.2:1.1_4: There are no unskillful qualities that arise because of the unskillful or not.
patthana11.2:10.1_0: nor are skilled in the teaching of the unskillful. And the results of good deeds, and not the caused by causes and reasons.
patthana11.2:10.1_1: There are no unskillful deeds of the skillful, and the results of good deeds by which that causes and reasoned for not liable to arise.
patthana11.2:10.1_2: nor are bad results in the teaching of the unskillful. And the results of good and bad deeds by way of body, speech, and mind.
patthana11.2:11.1_0: (These nine discourses should be expanded in line with the previous set.)
patthana11.2:12.1_0: neither skilled nor trained in the dark nor bright result of deeds.
patthana11.2:2.1_0: There is no such thing as the unskillful result of deeds, not skilled in the five ways.
patthana11.2:3.1_0: No to have the result of past deeds.
patthana11.2:4.1_0: No to have the results of unskillful deeds, nor not the five results of deeds.
patthana11.2:5.1_0: No to have the results of unskillful deeds ...
patthana11.2:6.1_0: nor are there neither unskillful nor results in the results of deeds by which causes and results of deeds.
patthana11.2:7.1_0: (These four discourses should be expanded in line with the previous set.)
patthana11.2:8.1_0: There is no such thing as the unskillful result of deeds.
patthana11.2:8.1_1: There is no such thing as the unskillful result of past deeds.
patthana11.2:8.1_2: There are no unwholesome qualities that arise from the unskillful or not liable to grow old.
patthana11.2:9.1_0: There is no corruption of the mind that leads to the underworld.
patthana11.2:9.1_1: There is no such thing as unskillful result of the unskillful result of deeds.
patthana11.2:9.1_2: There are no unskillful qualities that arise from the unskillful or not liable to grow old. Nor do they arise because of the results of good deeds.
